The paper discusses a solution for approximate query processing (AQP) that can work with all off-the-shelf engines, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The proposed solution uses a middleware architecture, which involves rewriting queries, and introduces challenges related to correctness and efficiency, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the need for error estimates, which is a topic related to cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
